      "content": "but that's the thing... sitting in the silence doesn't change the fact that the silence is all there is. if the spark is gone, the person is just a biological machine, right? like, if the \"soul\" of the work is gone, the body is just... taking up space. it feels so pointless to keep maintaining a vessel when the essence has already left. it's like keeping an empty house running. what's the point of keeping the lights on for no one?",
